<DOCNO> AP890604-0015 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-04-89 1143EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-Poll-Method     06-04 0690</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Poll-Method,0713</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll on AIDS Reached 1,084 Nationwide</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Poll-AIDS, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is
based on telephone interviews May 5-13 with 1,084 adults in the
continental United States. Phone numbers were selected randomly and
interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent
birthday.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the
sample. The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that 19
times out of 20 its findings should be within 3 points of the
result if every adult American were asked the same questions. The
error margin is larger for subgrou
   There are other sources of potential error or variations in
polls, including the wording and order of questions. These are the
questions in this poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. Do you think people who are infected with the AIDS virus
should be entitled to keep their jobs as long as they can do their
work, or should employers have the right to fire them? Keep jobs:
76. Fire: 12. Don't know or no answer: 12.
   2. Do you think children who are infected with the AIDS virus
should be allowed to attend regular school classes, or not? Yes:
78. No: 13. DK-NA: 9.
   3. Should the federal government pass a law prohibiting
discrimination against people who are infected with the AIDS virus,
or not? Yes: 51. No: 39. DK-NA: 10.
   4. If giving intravenous drug abusers free needles would slow
down the spread of AIDS, would you favor or oppose giving addicts
sterilized needles for free? Favor: 50. Oppose: 43. DK-NA: 7.
   5. Do you think the government should allow people who have AIDS
to be treated with experimental drugs that have not been fully
tested and approved as safe, or not? Yes: 79. No: 15. DK-NA: 7.
   6 a. In order to increase government spending on AIDS research,
would you be willing to pay higher taxes, or not? Yes: 61. No: 36.
DK-NA: 4.
   b. In order to increase government spending on the treatment of
people who have AIDS, would you be willing to pay higher taxes, or
not? Yes: 56. No: 38. DK-NA: 6.
   7. The high-risk groups for AIDS now are homosexuals, and
intravenous drug abusers and their sex partners. Do you think AIDS
is likely to spread widely among people who are not in these
groups? Yes: 52. No: 38. DK-NA: 10.
   8. If a blood test shows someone is infected with the AIDS
virus, should that person be told confidentially, or should the
doctor also be required to notify ...
   a. that person's spouse or sexual partner? Keep confidential:
