<HEAD>Plane Crashes Into Mountain Killing 4</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUESCA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescue workers scaled a mountain in the
Pyrenees on Sunday to recover the bodies of four people whose small
plane crashed on a flight from Morocco to France, authorities said.
   Earlier Sunday, a civil guard helicopter spotted the wreckage of
the plane 8,250 feet up Aneto Mountain, the provincial civil
government's office said.
   Barcelona airport reported the plane misssing Saturday night.
   Rescue workers recovered the bodies of the four French nationals
from the ice-covered peak and took them the morgue in the town of
Benasque.
