<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--IvoryBan     06-04 0078</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Ivory Ban,0080</SECOND>
<HEAD>France Bans Ivory Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   France is banning imports of ivory to help save
African elephants, the government announced Sunday.
   Brice Lalonde, the environment minister, said the import
prohibition will take effect Monday.
   Experts estimate that the African elephant population has
dwindled to half a million under pressure from poachers who kill
elephants for their tusks.
   France currently imports $3 million worth of ivory annually,
most of it processed in Hong Kong.
</TEXT>
