<FIRST>r i AM-SriLanka-Floods     06-04 0305</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Sri Lanka-Floods,0315</SECOND>
<HEAD>Landslides, Flooding Kill at Least 171</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PATRICK CRUEZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Floods and landslides caused by
torrential rains killed 171 people and wiped out entire hamlets in
the hills of central Sri Lanka, officials said Sunday.
   More than 100,000 people were homeless after eight inches of
rain drenched central farming regions in the pre-dawn hours of
Sunday, said Mahinda Premawardene, deputy director of the Social
Services Department. The rains had eased by late afternoon Sunday
but continued to hamper search operations.
   The hardest-hit area was the rubber, coconut and tea plantation
region around Kegalle, 45 miles northeast of Colombo. Mud and
stones loosened by a month of steady monsoon rain cascaded down
mountain slopes.
   ``We used our bare hands to dig into tons of mud to find
bodies,'' said local police Sgt. Madumma Banda. ``People from all
walks of life helped the police and troops.''
   He said landslides occurred in at least 10 areas of the Kegalle
district and blocked the main highway from Colombo to the Buddhist
religious center and resort town of Kandy.
   In Bulathkopitiya, 10 miles south of Kegalle, rescue workers
pulled 86 bodies from the landslide that buried the entire
community.
   Other deaths occurred in the neighboring villages of Pinndeniya,
Yatiyantota and Dedigama, Banda said.
   Most rural inhabitants live in shanties made of mud, sticks and
dried palm leaves that aren't made to resist monsoon rains.
   In Ratnapura, Sri Lanka's gem-mining center 45 miles southeast
of Colombo, six people died and flood waters were seven feet deep,
according to police inspector Hector Dharmasiri. Some people
reported flood waters of up to 30 feet deep, he said.
   Two people were crushed by rain-loosened boulders that rolled
down a slope in Nuwara Eliya, a resort town 65 miles east of
Colombo, police said.
</TEXT>
