<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--NuclearTest     06-04 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Nuclear Test,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>France Explodes Nuclear Bomb in South Pacific</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WELLINGTON, New Zealand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   France exploded a 20-kiloton
nuclear bomb at an underground site in French Polynesia on Sunday,
New Zealand government scientists said.
   The explosion, the third conducted by France this year, probably
occurred on the Pacific atoll of Mururoa, the Department of
Scientific and Industrial Research said.
   The department said it recorded the explosion on a seismograph.
   There was no immediate comment from French officials.
   The test was the 106th in France's underground series. The
previous test, on May 20, measured two kilotons.
</TEXT>
