<FIRST>r w BC-Judges-InvestmentsList 14-Takes   06-04 0607</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Judges-Investments List, 14-Takes,600</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the 935 federal judges whose
financial disclosure statements were examined by The Associated
Press.
   The list gives each judge's court and arange that approximates
the dollar amount of the net value of his investments.
   It should be noted that some of the judges appear to be in debt
when that may not be true. This is because the government reporting
system understates assets and can overstate liabilities.
   The figures on this list were computed by subtracting the range
for a judge's debts from the range for his investments. This
occasionally produces a transposed range for disclosed net
investment portfolio because the ranges for debts and assets may be
in varying sizes.
   In some cases, where the judge's form was filled out incorrectly
but the intent was clear, minor interpretation was used by the AP
in summarizing a judge's finances. In other cases, where more than
one interpretation was possible, finances were recorded exactly as
they were on the form.
